            </para>
          </schedule.amendments.group2>
          <schedule.amendments.group2 id="DLM2996939" toc="yes">
            <heading>Dietary Supplements Regulations 1985 (SR 1985/208)</heading>
            <para>
              <text>Regulation 12(2): omit <amend.in quote="1">Food Regulations 1984</amend.in> and substitute <amend.in quote="1">Australia–New Zealand Joint Food Standards Agreement as defined by the Food Act <changeable>2010</changeable></amend.in>.</text>
            </para>
          </schedule.amendments.group2>
          <schedule.amendments.group2 id="DLM2996940" toc="yes">
            <heading>Fisheries (Licensed Fish Receivers) Regulations 1997 (SR 1997/291)</heading>
            <para>
              <text>Regulation 5(1)(a): omit <amend.in quote="1">Food Hygiene Regulations 1974</amend.in> and substitute <amend.in quote="1">Food Act <changeable>2010</changeable></amend.in>.</text>
            </para>
            <para>
              <text>Regulation 5(1)(b): revoke.</text>
            </para>
          </schedule.amendments.group2>
          <schedule.amendments.group2 id="DLM2996941" toc="yes">
            <heading>Food Act Commencement Order 1984 (SR 1984/178)</heading>
            <para>
              <text>Revoke.</text>
            </para>
          </schedule.amendments.group2>
          <schedule.amendments.group2 id="DLM2996942" toc="yes">
            <heading>Food (Fees and Charges) Regulations 1997 (SR 1997/100)</heading>
            <para>
              <text>Revoke.</text>
            </para>
          </schedule.amendments.group2>
          <schedule.amendments.group2 id="DLM2996943" toc="yes">
            <heading>Hazardous Substances (Classes 6, 8, and 9 Controls) Regulations 2001 (SR 2001/117)</heading>
            <para>
              <text>Definition of <emphasis style="bold">food</emphasis> in regulation 3: omit <amend.in quote="1">section 2 of the Food Act 1981</amend.in> and substitute <amend.in quote="1"><changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 8</citation></changeable> of the Food Act <changeable>2010</changeable></amend.in>.</text>
            </para>
          </schedule.amendments.group2>
          <schedule.amendments.group2 id="DLM2996944" toc="yes">
            <heading>Hazardous Substances (Minimum Degrees of Hazard) Regulations 2001 (SR 2001/112)</heading>
            <para>
              <text>Definition of <emphasis style="bold">food</emphasis> in regulation 6(2): omit <amend.in quote="1">section 2 of the Food Act 1981</amend.in> and substitute <amend.in quote="1"><changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 8</citation></changeable> of the Food Act <changeable>2010</changeable></amend.in>.</text>
            </para>
            <para>
              <text>Definition of <emphasis style="bold">food additive</emphasis> in regulation 6(2): omit <amend.in quote="1">section 2(1) of the Food Regulations 1984 (SR 1984/262)</amend.in> and substitute <amend.in quote="1">standard 1.3 of the code incorporated into New Zealand law by the New Zealand (Australia New Zealand Food Standards Code) Food Standards 2002, issued under section 11C of the Food Act 1981 and known as the Food Standards Code</amend.in>.</text>
            </para>
          </schedule.amendments.group2>
          <schedule.amendments.group2 id="DLM2996945" toc="yes">
            <heading>Sale of Liquor Regulations 1990 (SR 1990/61)</heading>
            <para>
              <text>Condition (c) in Form 7 of Schedule 1: revoke and substitute:</text>
              <amend quote="1">
                <subprov skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>(if the licence applies to premises described in section 36(1)(d) of the Act) the only liquor that may be sold is—</text>
                    <label-para quote="1" skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">i</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>wine, sparkling wine, fruit wine, sparkling fruit wine, vegetable wine, sparkling vegetable wine, mead, and beer that conforms with a food standard made under the Food Act <changeable>2010</changeable>; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para quote="1" skeleton="no">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">ii</label>
                      <para>
                        <text>liquor in a food condiment if the condiment has been prepared for culinary purposes and rendered unsuitable for drinking:</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </subprov>
              </amend>
              <follow-text space-before="no">.</follow-text>
            </para>
          </schedule.amendments.group2>
          <schedule.amendments.group2 id="DLM2996946" toc="yes">
            <heading>Weights and Measures Regulations 1999 (SR 1999/373)</heading>
            <para>
              <text>Definition of <emphasis style="bold">spirit dispenser</emphasis> in regulation 2: omit <amend.in quote="1">regulations 233 to 233H of the Food Regulations 1984</amend.in> and substitute <amend.in quote="1">standard 2.7.5 of the code incorporated into New Zealand law by the New Zealand (Australia New Zealand Food Standards Code) Food Standards 2002, issued under section 11C of the Food Act 1981 and known as the Food Standards Code</amend.in>.</text>
            </para>
          </schedule.amendments.group2>
          <schedule.amendments.group2 id="DLM2996947" toc="yes">
            <heading>Wine Regulations 2006 (SR 2006/147)</heading>
            <para>
              <text>Regulation 4(4): revoke and substitute:</text>
              <amend quote="1">
                <subprov quote="1" skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">4</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>For wine to which regulations 7 and 8 do not apply, the name or description of the wine shown on the label of wine must not include any reference to a single variety of grape unless the wine has been manufactured from not less than 75% by volume of juice derived from that variety of grape.</text>
                  </para>
                </subprov>
                <subprov quote="1" skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes" quote="1">5</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>For wine to which regulations 7 and 8 do not apply, the name or description of the wine shown on the label of wine must not include any reference to 2 or more varieties of grape unless the wine has been manufactured from not less than 75% by volume of juice derived from those varieties of grape and the names of the varieties of grape are listed on the label in descending order of proportion.</text>
                  </para>
                </subprov>
              </amend>
            </para>
          </schedule.amendments.group2>
        </schedule.amendments.group1>
